14:53.660 --> 14:56.661
Oh. That watch was the only
thing that made me not terrible.

14:56.663 --> 14:58.263
I can't lose it.

14:58.265 --> 15:01.432
I'll drop another rock
a few feet to the left.

15:03.703 --> 15:06.271
My other eye!

15:06.273 --> 15:07.505
Ow!

15:07.507 --> 15:10.775
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

15:10.777 --> 15:13.411
Not a single one
has missed me!

15:16.283 --> 15:17.682
What are you doing?

15:17.684 --> 15:21.686
That expert at the school said
trophies are bad for kids.

15:21.688 --> 15:24.122
It's all part of GRIT.

15:24.124 --> 15:25.723
No, no.

15:25.725 --> 15:27.792
My trophies were earned.

15:27.794 --> 15:29.527
Even the soccer one?

15:29.529 --> 15:32.630
I went to most
of the practices.

15:32.632 --> 15:35.033
Yeah, but what happens
when another parenting expert

15:35.035 --> 15:38.202
comes along with a whole
new theory on self-esteem?

15:38.204 --> 15:39.704
Another expert?

15:39.706 --> 15:41.439
Who are they?
What are they saying?

15:45.545 --> 15:46.778
Aw.

15:52.986 --> 15:54.719
Okay, the watch is gone.

15:54.721 --> 15:57.555
I guess I can live with being
a useless, worthless nothing

15:57.557 --> 15:59.090
as long as no one finds out.

15:59.092 --> 16:02.660
Sweetie, your grampa's
on the phone.

16:02.662 --> 16:03.661
Hello.

16:03.663 --> 16:05.229
Great news, kiddo.

16:05.231 --> 16:07.565
<i> Remember That</i> magazine
is putting out

16:07.567 --> 16:10.001
their annual
family heirlooms issue.

16:10.003 --> 16:11.736
They want us for the cover.

16:11.738 --> 16:13.771
You, me and the pocket watch.

16:13.773 --> 16:14.906
Um...

16:14.908 --> 16:17.075
It's a great story.

16:17.076 --> 16:19.243
Passing a beloved heirloom
from grandfather to grandson.

16:19.245 --> 16:22.680
A gift that restored
a child's faith in himself.

16:22.682 --> 16:25.583
Uh, Grampa, there's something
I have to tell you.

16:25.585 --> 16:26.751
Hold on one second.

16:26.753 --> 16:28.252
I'm just finishing up

16:28.254 --> 16:30.588
a mandatory
pre-article heart exam.

16:30.590 --> 16:32.423
Doc says as long
as I don't suffer

16:32.425 --> 16:35.360
any major disappointments,
I'll be fine.

16:35.362 --> 16:37.428
Now, what did you want
to tell me?

16:37.430 --> 16:39.697
Uh, helmets ruined football.

16:39.699 --> 16:41.766
Exactly! If you want
to protect your head,

16:41.768 --> 16:43.101
grow your hair long.

16:43.103 --> 16:45.870
Anyway, I'll see you
tomorrow at 10:00 a.m.

16:45.872 --> 16:49.273
And you won't be late
because you've got that watch.

16:49.275 --> 16:50.808
(groans)

16:50.810 --> 16:52.777
Stupid parenting experts.

16:52.779 --> 16:55.780
Why don't they write a book
called<i> Stop Buying These Books?</i>

16:55.782 --> 16:57.448
Everybody'd buy that.

16:57.450 --> 16:59.550
Even if I was listening
to what you said,

16:59.552 --> 17:01.619
it doesn't matter;
nothing matters.

17:01.621 --> 17:03.454
My trophy business
has failed

17:03.456 --> 17:05.490
and Bart has the
thing I wanted most:

17:05.492 --> 17:07.058
Grampa's watch.

17:07.060 --> 17:08.059
What watch?

17:08.061 --> 17:10.561
The one you get
for being a success.

17:10.563 --> 17:11.963
Well, then I should have it.

17:11.965 --> 17:14.132
Uh, that never really came up.

17:14.134 --> 17:17.535
All that's left to do now
is bring these to the needy.

17:19.406 --> 17:21.806
Best I can do
is charge you ten dollars

17:21.808 --> 17:23.307
to throw them
in my Dumpster.

17:23.309 --> 17:26.077
How about I give you a trophy
that says "Best Pawn Shop"?

17:26.079 --> 17:27.812
Not unless I earned it.

17:27.814 --> 17:28.713
(gasps)

17:30.316 --> 17:31.649
Dad's watch!

17:31.651 --> 17:32.817
Hey, dirtbag shopkeep.

17:32.819 --> 17:34.519
How did this come to you?

17:34.521 --> 17:35.920
Mm. Some kid
brought it in.

17:35.922 --> 17:37.655
Said he was mad
at his friend

17:37.657 --> 17:41.659
for dropping so many rocks
in his eye.

17:41.661 --> 17:43.728
That dude's seen
a lot of living.

17:45.265 --> 17:47.165
Yours for 20 bucks.

17:47.167 --> 17:48.699
That's an insult.

17:48.701 --> 17:50.935
You're talking about a
self-worth-boosting antique

17:50.937 --> 17:53.538
that's been in my family
for generations.

17:53.540 --> 17:54.772
Twenty-two?

17:54.774 --> 17:56.908
You'll take it all
and you'll like it.

18:01.514 --> 18:03.681
(maniacal laugh)

18:03.683 --> 18:05.516
Yes. I have it.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.018
Some said it would never happen.

18:07.020 --> 18:09.020
Most were unaware
of the situation.

18:09.022 --> 18:12.123
But I finally have
my father's watch!

18:12.125 --> 18:14.192
(maniacal laugh)

18:16.696 --> 18:20.131
(singsongy): Oh, Bart,
look what Daddy's got now.

18:20.133 --> 18:22.600
(Bart crying)

18:23.703 --> 18:27.538
Grampa was the only person
who believed in me.

18:27.540 --> 18:29.974
But when he finds out
I lost the watch,

18:29.976 --> 18:31.375
even he'll give up.

18:31.377 --> 18:32.543
(sobbing)

18:32.545 --> 18:33.711
Stay strong, Homer.

18:33.713 --> 18:35.379
Don't go soft on him now.

18:35.381 --> 18:37.915
This is a once-in-a-lifetime
face-rubbing-in.

18:37.917 --> 18:39.650
Mm. Come on, foot.

18:39.652 --> 18:40.885
Kick, damn you!

18:40.887 --> 18:41.953
(grunts)

18:43.490 --> 18:47.725
(sighs) Son, I found something
that belongs to you.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.894
(gasps) Grampa's watch!

18:49.896 --> 18:51.896
No. I can't take it.

18:51.898 --> 18:53.731
I didn't earn it,
so I don't deserve it.

18:53.733 --> 18:55.233
You were right.

18:55.235 --> 18:56.901
I am a screwup.

18:56.903 --> 19:00.438
But, boy,
who screwed you up?

19:00.440 --> 19:02.406
(gasps) You.

19:02.408 --> 19:04.008
It was you.

19:04.010 --> 19:06.677
And those who came before.

19:08.615 --> 19:10.281
(choking loudly)

19:13.920 --> 19:15.920
